Reference-contexts: Related Research on Scientific Discovery Our approach to computational discovery draws many ideas from earlier work on the topic. As we noted in Section 2, our system shares many goals and techniques with Valdes-Perez' Mechem, which discovers reaction pathways in physical chemistry. Another close relative is SynGen <ref> (Hendrickson, 1995) </ref>, which addresses the task of chemical synthesis in which one must determine not only the reaction paths but also the starting molecules. A more detailed similarity is that both ASTRA and SynGen generate pathways by chaining backward from the final products using known reactions.
